<DOC><DOCNO> AP900102-0035 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-02-90 0811EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--India-Nudity     01-02 0136</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--India-Nudity,0140</SECOND><HEAD>Horses Enlisted to Combat Nude Sunbathing</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police losing their war on nudesunbathing by foreign tourists in the beach resort of Goa went backto nature to escalate their fight _ they're going on horseback.   Mounted police patrols will ``be trained in arresting theculprits on the beach,'' the United News of India reported today.   It quoted a police official as saying the five horses werebrought from New Delhi, 850 miles to the northeast, in an effort tohalt ``nudism and drug peddling on Goa beaches frequented byhippies and anti-social elements.''   There was no explanation why police on horseback might succeedwhere their comrades on foot and in motor vehicles have failed inthe former Portuguese enclave on India's western coast 170 milessouth of Bombay.</TEXT></DOC>